    Greek fan stabbed to death
 Athens: A soccer fan was stabbed to death and another hospitalised after they were attacked following a Greek Cup match between Olympiakos Piraeus and Panathinaikos, police said on Thursday. The two Olympiakos fans were attacked outside a cafe in Loutsa, a coastal town just outside Athens, by a group of Panathinaikos fans in the early hours of Thursday.
 Chelsea fined pound;40,000
 London: Chelsea were fined pound;40,000 ($78,540) on Thursday for the disorderly behaviour during their 2-0 Premier League win over Derby County on November 24. An FA statement said the charge followed the players rsquo; conduct towards referee Andre Marriner after Ghana midfielder Michael Essien had been sent off. 
