 PCB asks for allowance 
 Karachi: The PCB has asked the ICC for a $5000 per month allowance for its directors during the Champions Trophy to be held here in October-November. According to a newspaper report, the PCB made the proposal during a recent meeting between PCB officials and the ICC in Dubai. The ICC has said that it would get back to the PCB this March. 
 Aunshuman to contest 3 posts 
 Vadodara: Former India opener and coach Aunshuman Gaekwad will be contesting three posts in the Baroda Cricket Association rsquo;s elections on Friday mdash; vice-president, joint secretary and managing committee member mdash; as an independent candidate.
 Anand draws
 Wijk Aan Zee: Viswanathan Anand played out yet another draw, this time with Levon Aronian of Armenia, in the fifth round of the Corus International Chess Tournament on Thursday.

 Playing black, Anand settled for his fourth straight draw. The Indian inched up to two points while Aronian took his tally to 3.5 points. 
